			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64119515"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64119515"><p>One had quality lead actors, the other had supporting actors getting their big shot at lead roles.</p><p>The writing had similar issues; in The Firth Element you had screenwriter Robert Mark Kamen (who wrote The Karate Kid) with Luc Besson tacking his name on, in Valerian you had Besson trying to write something on his own.</p><p>But without Bruce Willis and Milla Jovovich it could have been really awful, with everything else the same.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64119515">

